@JobScoreServer_HostAddress = http://localhost:5041

### Test Weather Forecast (no auth required)
GET {{JobScoreServer_HostAddress}}/weatherforecast/
Accept: application/json

###

### Register a new user (regular user, not admin)
POST {{JobScoreServer_HostAddress}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!",
  "passwordConfirm": "Password123!"
}

###

### Login as regular user
POST {{JobScoreServer_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

###

### Create Job Description as authenticated user (userId extracted from cookie)
### Must be logged in first!
POST {{JobScoreServer_HostAddress}}/api/jobdescription
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Senior Software Engineer",
  "content": "We are looking for a rockstar ninja who can leverage synergies..."
}

###

### Try to create Job Description without login (should fail - 401 Unauthorized)
POST {{JobScoreServer_HostAddress}}/api/jobdescription
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Job Title",
  "content": "Job content"
}

###

### Try to access Rules as regular user (should fail - 403 Forbidden)
GET {{JobScoreServer_HostAddress}}/api/rule
Accept: application/json

###

### Login as admin (you'll need to manually create an admin user in DB first)
POST {{JobScoreServer_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@jobscore.com",
  "password": "AdminPassword123!"
}

###

### Access Rules as admin (should succeed - 200 OK)
GET {{JobScoreServer_HostAddress}}/api/rule
Accept: application/json

###

### Update Rule Weights as admin (should succeed - 200 OK)
### Note: Sum of all weights must equal 100
PUT {{JobScoreServer_HostAddress}}/api/rule/weights
Content-Type: application/json

[
  {
    "id": 1,
    "weight": 30
  },
  {
    "id": 2,
    "weight": 25
  },
  {
    "id": 3,
    "weight": 20
  },
  {
    "id": 4,
    "weight": 15
  },
  {
    "id": 5,
    "weight": 10
  }
]

###

### Try to update with invalid weights (sum != 100, should fail - 400 Bad Request)
PUT {{JobScoreServer_HostAddress}}/api/rule/weights
Content-Type: application/json

[
  {
    "id": 1,
    "weight": 50
  },
  {
    "id": 2,
    "weight": 30
  }
]

###

### Try to update weights as regular user (should fail - 403 Forbidden)
### First login as regular user, then try this request
PUT {{JobScoreServer_HostAddress}}/api/rule/weights
Content-Type: application/json

[
  {
    "id": 1,
    "weight": 40
  },
  {
    "id": 2,
    "weight": 60
  }
]

###
